result.execSummary:
The defendant Daishun S Dixson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Daishun S Dixson in court, in custody.  Attorney Haley E Wentz in court for Daishun S Dixson.  Attorney Dax Odom in court for State of Wisconsin. 
Case in court for Plea and Sentencing Hearing.  State advised the Court they have complied with the Victims' Rights Law. 
Parties have reached a resolution. State placed negotiations on the record. Defense counsel and defendant confirms. 
Court is in receipt of the; Plea Questionnaire, Addendum and WIS JI- Criminal/ Elements of the Offense.


AS TO COUNTS 1 and 3: 
PLEA HEARING HELD:  Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.  
Defendant advised that if he is not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible. Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights. 
Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. State consents to the Jury Waiver. Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. 
Court ordered a DNA sample and advised defendant of applicable surcharge. 

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.    

AS TO COUNT 1:
Defendant ordered to serve 60 DAYS in the House of Correction, STRAIGHT TIME, with credit of 12 days time served, and CONCURRENT to count 3. Court STAYED the sentence and placed the defendant on probation for 2 years. This case to run CONSECUTIVE with cases 21CM2821, 21CM3196, and 22CM1649.

AS TO COUNT 3:
Defendant ordered to serve 60 DAYS in the House of Correction, STRAIGHT TIME, with credit of 12 days time served, and CONCURRENT to count 1. Court STAYED the sentence and placed the defendant on probation for 2 years. This case to run CONSECUTIVE with cases 21CM2821, 21CM3196, and 22CM1649.


WITH THE FOLLOWING CONDITIONS: 
- Report to probation today.
- Pay all mandatory court costs, fees, and surcharges. Payable in 2 years or civil judgment. 
- Court waives all non mandatory court costs due to inability to pay. 
- AODA assessment and compliance with treatment.
- Maintain Absolute sobriety.
- Random drug and breath tests.
- Mental health assessment and compliance with any treatment. 
- Successfully complete a behavioral and cognitive thinking program. 
- No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause.
- Obtain/maintain full time work. 
- Restitution set at ZERO.
- Submit a DNA sample and pay the surcharge during probation.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment. 
- 10 HOURS of community service. 
- No Contact with: KD, ML, AL
- Defendant advised of his right to appeal.


AS TO COUNT 2  - Pursuant to negotiations and on the Motion of the State, Court Ordered Charge DISMISSED BUT READ IN for the purpose of sentencing.
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief, filed.
Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum to Plea
Jury Instructions Disorderly Conduct, filed.
Jury Instructions Resisting, filed.
Pretrial Incarceration Credit, filed.
